{
  "stem": "20711.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Toward the end, the last two, three weeks-- but for six weeks I was definitely all by myself.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But toward the very end, my father arrived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father, who happened to be transferred from the [INAUDIBLE] ghetto with most of those selected people into a safer area, because [INAUDIBLE] was at the Slovakian border.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And there was a lot of partisan activity there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Some of the Jewish people, including my stepfather, who was also-- later, stepfather-- who was also important at camp escaped and became a partisan.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And that find very dangerous surroundings.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So they decided to take them to the trans-Danube area, which was far more safer.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And this people was taken into that new location.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And if you ever read or heard about the face of that camp, which called the Pusztavam, everybody was murdered there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And to my greatest surprise, all the books who mention the Pusztavam, they just say all those saved doctors and lawyers and important intellectuals, they all perished after they were forced to dig their own grave.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And nobody knew there was three survivors.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And one of them happened to be my father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I even knew the other two guys.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "One was a dentist.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "The other was a doctor of internal medicine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not to the doctor, but I remember the dentist, because he became my dentist after the war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was Szasz, Karoly, a very nice, big, strong man.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I do remember the doctor, too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He happened to be my doctor, too.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But he had a very common Jewish name, and I am not sure if I-- [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Fleischman ?] or something like that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they happened to be out of town of Pusztavam together with a guard.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
